Shortcut commands for future rendering
1. Install once
python -m pip install markdown
2. Render any markdown file
python Utilities&Prompts/render_md_table_to_png.py InterviewQuestion_Notes/YourFile.md
3. If python is not on PATH
```bash
C:/Users/Sanket/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python314/python.exe Utilities&Prompts/render_md_table_to_png.py InterviewQuestion_Notes/YourFile.md
```
4. PowerShell alias for faster reuse
```powershell
function md2png { & 'C:/Users/Sanket/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python314/python.exe' 'C:/Users/Sanket/VSCodeProjects/LearningPlaywright3X/Utilities&Prompts/render_md_table_to_png.py' @args }
# then run:
# md2png InterviewQuestion_Notes/YourFile.md
```
Result
This creates InterviewQuestion_Notes/YourFile.png
It preserves the original .md file and saves the rendered image next to it
